iv>\n          <pre class=\"overflow-x-auto font-mono text-sm leading-7 text-pirate-text\"><code><span class=\"text-pirate-muted\">// bring your own keys</span>\nconst ide = new PirateDev({\n  aiMarkup: 0,\n  lockIn: false,\n  deployTarget: 'your-vps'\n})\n\nawait ide.agent.build(\n  'ship the thing',\n  { provider: 'your-choice' }\n)</code></pre>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id=\"problem\" class=\"border-b border-pirate-line px-5 py-24 lg:px-8\">\n      <div class=\"mx-auto max-w-7xl\">\n        <p class=\"font-mono text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-pirate-muted\">The Problem</p>\n        <h2 class=\"mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl\">Every Cloud IDE Takes a Cut.</h2>\n        <div class=\"mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3\">\n          <article class=\"rounded-lg border border-pirate-line bg-pirate-ink p-6 transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-white/50\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-xl font-black text-white\">Replit</h3>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 text-pirate-muted\">AI requests can land at 10-20x raw model cost. Fast, polished, and expensive when the agent runs hot.</p>\n          </article>\n          <article class=\"rounded-lg border border-pirate-line bg-pirate-ink p-6 transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-white/50\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-xl font-black text-white\">Codespaces</h3>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 text-pirate-muted\">Great if Azure is your harbor. Less great when your workflow needs to leave Microsoft's map.</p>\n          </article>\n          <article class=\"rounded-lg border border-pirate-line bg-pirate-ink p-6 transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-white/50\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-xl font-black text-white\">Cursor</h3>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 text-pirate-muted\">Twenty bucks a month for model access you could wire directly, plus limits when the queue gets loud.</p>\n          </article>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id=\"solution\" class=\"border-b border-pirate-line bg-pirate-ink px-5 py-24 lg:px-8\">\n      <div class=\"mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-center\">\n        <div>\n          <p class=\"font-mono text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-pirate-muted\">The Solution</p>\n          <h2 class=\"mt-4 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl\">Zero Markup. Zero Apologies.</h2>\n          <p class=\"mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-pirate-muted\">Bring your own API keys. PirateDev passes model usage through at $0 markup, then charges only for compute. Your keys, your providers, your bill.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-lg border border-white/15 bg-pirate-black p-6\">\n          <div class=\"grid gap-3 font-mono text-sm\">\n            <div class=\"grid grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-4 border-b border-pirate-line pb-4 text-pirate-muted\">\n              <span>Model path</span><span>Typical request</span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"grid grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-4 border-b border-pirate-line py-4\">\n              <span>GPT-4o on Cursor</span><span class=\"text-white\">~$0.15</span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"grid grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-4 pt-4\">\n              <span>GPT-4o on PirateDev</span><span class=\"text-white\">~$0.01</span>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"mt-5 text-sm text-pirate-muted\">Actual API cost varies by provider, context, and output size. The markup stays dead.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id=\"features\" class=\"border-b border-pirate-line px-5 py-24 lg:px-8\">\n      <div class=\"mx-auto max-w-7xl\">\n        <p class=\"font-mono text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-pirate-muted\">Features</p>\n        <h2 class=\"mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl\">The IDE your agent deserves.</h2>\n        <div